nodes.text: Theenwine was a type of wine. In the year 14 BBY, Moff Delian Mors of the Galactic Empire had a young Imperial lieutenant in her service provide three cases of Theenwine as a parting gift to Nashi the Hutt, an envoy of the crime lord Jabba Desilijic Tiure, who was visiting Mors in her command center on the planet Ryloth's largest moon.
Theenwine was first mentioned in the novel Lords of the Sith, which was written by Paul S. Kemp and released in 2015.
